40|$|Scattering {{mechanisms}} that involve edge waves are addressed. The behavior of edge waves and their interaction with flat, perfectly conducting plates are {{depicted in the}} time domain through a visualization of <b>surface</b> <b>currents</b> that flow on the surface, as an incident Gaussian pulse of energy washes over the surface. Viewing these <b>surface</b> <b>currents</b> allows a very clear physical interpretation and appreciation of the scattering process...|$|R
